    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - High-pressure Oil System - Removal -
        High-pressure Oil Pump Cover
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Pump Cover</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the dual turbocharger assembly. See "Dual Turbocharger Assembly".</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the intake manifold and EGR cooler assembly. See "Manifolds and Exhaust Gas
                Recirculation (EGR)".
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001205" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>High-pressure oil pump cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 25 bolt (8)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove eight M6 x 25 bolts from the high-pressure oil pump cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001206" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>High-pressure oil pump cover sealant separation</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, cut Liquid Gasket (RTV) before lifting up high-pressure cover. The rear
                    cover gasket could be pulled up and out, requiring removal of the rear cover to replace gasket.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a thin gasket scraper to separate the sealant bond between crankcase, rear cover, and
                high-pressure oil pump cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After cutting sealant, lift the high-pressure oil pump cover straight up to clear pump
                gear.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the high-pressure pump cover gasket seal.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
